post_text:
ACS Supply Update:
Similar to last school year, the district will be providing student supplies. We are working hard to make sure every student has their own supplies for the 2020 - 2021 school year. We are asking parents to provide headphones/earbuds and water bottles. Any elementary family that would like to send in additional face masks to keep at school for their child is able to do so. The district will be providing two masks per child and have extra disposable masks if needed.

post_text: ACS Yearbook Update: Mrs. Donovan has been in contact with the yearbook representative all summer regarding yearbook arrival. They had expressed an August arrival. post_text:
This week it is ‚ÄúTeacher Appreciation‚Äù week. Like most things in the world right now, this week will look very different than other years. While our district was left emotional after last weeks news, announcing schools will remain closed for the rest of the academic year. We will recognize what is important.

Today, more than ever this quote holds strong. It is not about the classroom, but those who are educating our children and those who love each student unconditionally. We continue to work as a team to foster growth, safety, courage, and resiliency.

Today, we are all teachers. We are all educators. We want to thank our faculty and staff for their hard work. We also want to thank all the parents, siblings and family members who are working hard managing school, work, and the stresses of COVID-19. Together we will rise above. Together we will be stronger than ever. Continue working hard, continue fighting the good fight, and continue doing what is best for our kids. We appreciate ALL OF YOU! üíú

#ACSSTRONG

News from the ACS library!

Our spring reading challenge ends today. Students who participated by reading 375 minutes during the month of April and kept track of their reading minutes need to submit them to Mrs.Tidd.

Please complete the calendar (either the library‚Äôs calendar or one you created). At the bottom, be sure to neatly print your first and last name, your teacher‚Äôs name and have your parent sign it. Then please take a photo and email it to ctidd@acsghosts.org. Please do not throw the reading log away until you have received an email stating we received your log. If you are unable to email it please, put it in an envelope with Mrs.Tidd‚Äôs name on it and drop it off at school.

Thank you!

Stay positive! We are ACS STRONG!

COVID-19 - Meal Delivery Update

Alexandria will be moving to a one day a week meal delivery plan. As things continue to evolve in our county, we are doing what we can to eliminate exposure for our students and staff. The health and safety of everyone involved is our first priority. We will continue to delivery on Tuesday mornings. Please continue to have your bins, boxes, or coolers out for drop off. The delivery on Tuesday will include seven days of breakfast and lunch for each child in your household.

Please contact Ann Remington or Rod Tidd with any questions at (315) 482-9971. Again, we thank you for your patience and flexibility as we continue to change plans to ensure the safety of our ACS family.

In an effort to minimize the contact that each meal delivery undergoes, we ask that this week's delivery, you please place a cooler, a tote, a box, or a labeled bin at your curb for us to put the meals into. The bus will pull up, place the meals in the container you have left out, and the driver will honk the horn, so someone can retrieve the meals. If you do not have a container this week, we will leave the meals on your front step.

Thank you for working with us to support minimal exposure for the safety of our staff and families. We still love to see the kids, so please leave us a note or wave from the window. Seeing and hearing from our students makes our day!

March 15, 2020 COVID - 19 Meal Update.

ACS Cafeteria staff, bus drivers, administration, faculty and staff are ready to deliver meals to every child beginning at 10 am tomorrow.
- Beginning at 10 am the buses will follow normal routes, delivering two days worth of breakfast and lunch.
- This delivery pattern will happen Monday, Wednesday, Friday to ensure all kids are fed during the weekday and into the weekend.
- Concurrently, all village students can pick up food Monday, Wednesday, and Friday at the Reformed Church beginning at 10 am.
- If you would not like food delivered, please contact the cafeteria at aremington@acsghosts.org
